Years ago, the British found the French word ‘genievre’ too much trouble to pro- nounce and so they called it geneva. At any rate, genievre has nothing to do with Geneva; it means juniper, and juniper is the essential flavoring of nearly all gins. Other herbs, as the distiller chooses, lend their charms to produce varying flavors, which is why different brands, all good, have distinctive qualities. As usual, it’s a matter of taste.
